name: Carsties
description: An application demonstrating a microservice-based architecture with a Next.js frontend and an ASP.NET Core backend.

name: ContainerWorld
description: A collection of containerized projects designed to streamline development, deployment, and scalability for microservices, DevOps pipelines, and AI applications.

name: chatbot-builder-executor
description: The Langchain Execution Microservice for Chatbot Builder Application. Controlled by the Engine-Service, responsible for executing langchain logic in workflows.

name: Project-SignalWave
description: Project SIgnalWave is a modern, cloud-native application designed to demonstrate the implementation of microservices architectures within a Kubernetes cluster.

name: bookreads-Beginning-Spring-Boot-2
description: My study notes on the book `Beginning Spring Boot 2 Applications and Microservices with the Spring Framework - K. Siva Prasad Reddy`

name: Remote.Shell.Interrupt
description: React ForntEnd App and .NET WebAPI microservices. This application allows you interact with many VM by ssh automatically and executing bunch of command by schedule.

name: trench-test
description: A microservices-based web application for managing token data, AI services, trading operations, and user management using Docker, Kubernetes, and CI/CD with GitHub Actions.

name: spring-cloud-api-gateway
description: Spring Cloud API Gateway is the central point of entry for the application that has multiple instances of Microservices running behind the API Gateway. It will fetch URL from Eureka.

name: AD_User_Manager_SOAP_APIs
description: A Spring Boot-based microservice for managing Active Directory users and groups via SOAP APIs. Supports user creation, update, deletion, enable/disable, group retrieval, and adding/removing users from groups. Simplifies Active Directory integration for enterprise applications.

name: AdvaJobs
description: AdvaJobs is a job advertisement platform connecting job seekers and employers. Features include account management, secure login, job posting, and application management. Built with React (Vite.js), Java Spring Boot, and RESTful APIs using a microservices architecture.

name: level_up_project
description: Project I completed for a job interview for Brezna's Level Up program. It is a web application which implements Typescript, Next.js, React, NestJS, MySQL, Tailwind CSS, and Docker Container while the project was done in Microservice Architecture. The point of the application is to unify information from 3 providers with specific mapping.

name: SoftwareArchitectures-DesignPatterns2-CourseWork
description: This repository contains a Microservice-based backend application for managing Highway Tickets. Built with Spring Boot ,Spring Cloud Eureka ,Spring Cloud Config Server ,Spring Cloud Gateway, it streamlines ticket issuance, vehicle registration, user management, and internal payment processing. Comprehensive API testing using Postman

name: transcendence
description: Transcendence is a web application built with a Vue.js frontend and a Django backend, designed with a microservices architecture using Docker. It features robust monitoring and logging solutions powered by Grafana and the ELK stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana), ensuring seamless performance and observability.

name: AWS-Deployment
description: Conteneurisation des microservices avec Docker, orchestrés sur un cluster  Kubernetes (EKS) sur AWS.  Infrastructure gérée via Terraform  pour automatiser le  provisionnement d'instances EC2, bases de données RDS, et stockage sur S3.  Utilisation de CloudWatch, Prometheus, et Grafana pour surveiller les  performances de l'application en production.

name: PythonLearningFromZero
description: "Python from Zero to AI" – A journey of learning Python from scratch, documented step-by-step by a developer with 9 years of experience in web, backend, microservices, design patterns, and Azure. This repo explores Python basics to advanced AI concepts, tracking progress and insights for mastering Python and its AI applications
